# UI Components

This document outlines the UI component architecture and available component libraries.

## Component Libraries

### Primary UI Components
- **shadcn-nuxt 2.2+** - Main UI component collection using Radix Vue primitives
- **Radix Vue 1.9+** - Unstyled, accessible UI primitives
- **Reka UI 2.3+** - Additional UI components and utilities

### Component Structure
- Components are stored inside the `components/` folder
- shadcn components are in `components/ui/` following the shadcn-vue pattern
- Custom app-specific components like `Icon.vue` are in `components/App/` folder (used as `<AppIcon />`)
- Global custom components are stored in the root `components/` directory (e.g., `ColorMode.vue`)

## Available UI Components

### Core Components (shadcn/ui)
- **Button** - Various button styles and sizes
- **Card** - Card container with header, content, footer variants
- **Dialog** - Modal dialogs with overlay and content areas
- **Input** - Form input components
- **Select** - Dropdown selection components
- **Sheet** - Slide-out panels and drawers
- **Skeleton** - Loading placeholders
- **Pagination** - Page navigation components
- **Navigation Menu** - Complex navigation structures
- **Popover** - Floating content containers
- **Glowing Effect** - Custom animation component

### Specialized Components
- **VanishingInput** - Animated input component
- **NftCard** - NFT display component
- **NftModal** - NFT detail modal
- **RoomModal** - Room detail modal
- **MOCAMedia** - Media display component
- **MOCAModel** - 3D model display component
- **ChatInterface** - AI chat interface

## Animation & Effects
- **Motion-V 1.2+** - Vue animation library for component transitions
- **TailwindCSS Animate** - CSS animation utilities
- **tw-animate-css** - Additional animation classes

## Icons
- **@nuxt/icon 1.10+** - Icon management system
- **@iconify/vue** - Iconify integration
- **Lucide Vue Next** - Lucide icon set
- **Custom MOCA Icons** - Located in `svg/moca/` directory

## Layout Components
- **Vue Masonry Wall 5+** - Masonry grid layouts
- **@tanstack/vue-table 8.21+** - Advanced table components

## Usage Patterns

- Use shadcn/ui components as the foundation
- Extend with Radix Vue primitives when needed
- Create custom components in appropriate directories
- Follow the established naming conventions
- Use TypeScript for all component props and emits